div.p:
That hee that will adorne should use those of the better sort; and hee that will disgrace, should use those of the worse: as Simonides being to write an Ode in honour of the victory gotten in a Course by certaine Mules, being not well paid, called them by their name [
                        〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                     ] that signifies their propinquity to Asses: but having received a greater reward, Stiles them the sonnes of swift footed Coursers.
